  "summary": "Malicious code in next-form-helper (npm)",
  "details": "Next-form-helper@1.0.2 declares a circular self-dependency (\"next-form-helper\":\"^1.0.1\") that causes npm install to loop or fail during dependency resolution. Its postinstall hook runs `node rickroll.js`, which opens a YouTube video in the browser via the `open` package. No credential or token theft is present; this is a small (648-byte) install-disrupting nuisance/abuse package.",
